snippet.textDisplay: You guys should go to the Hotel Alex Johnson in Rapid City, South Dakota. I am a flight attendant and I stayed there during my layover. It was interesting.... apparently, there are 4 ghosts; Alex Johnson, The Lady in White, The Jilted bride, and Alex Johnson's niece.  The lady in white jumped out of her 8th-floor hotel window after being left at the altar and the whole 8th floor is supposedly haunted. Every time one of my friends has an overnight there, they have heard weird noises and have had their toiletries move around in the bathroom. When I stayed there everything seemed normal until 5:00 AM when the fire alarms and emergency evacuation announcements started going off all over the hotel. Everyone evacuated and the fire department came and found no reason that they would have been set off... It's a pretty neat hotel, although not great for sleeping lol

snippet.textDisplay:
Different Queen Mary’s by the way. The Queen Mary ship was built for Queen Mary who was King George’s wife. She was born in 1867 which is 325 years later then when Queen Mary of Scots was born. Queen Mary of Scots was also known as Mary Stuart, she reined over Scotland from 1542 (approximately six days after she was born) from 1567 (20 years before her death). These Queens were completely different but it’s still coincidental that her name happened to be Queen Mary.
Now anyone who’s wondering won’t have to do research (:
